## 1. 🐛 Bug Detection

| File | Issue | Severity | Detail |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `mcp_server/server.py` | Silent Background Failures | **HIGH** | `_db_pool.submit(_save_inference)` logs errors but has no retry mechanism. If the database is locked (common in SQLite), inferences are permanently lost. |
| `dashboard/app.py` | Heuristic Fragility | **MEDIUM** | `_map_github_to_features` uses deterministic estimates for CPU/Memory (Line 461) based on build duration. This is highly inaccurate and introduces artificial noise into the ML model's inference loop. |
| `drift_monitor.py` | PSI Bias | **LOW** | Epsilon smoothing (1e-4) is applied before re-normalization. While it prevents crashes, it can slightly skew PSI results on extremely sparse data. |
| `mcp_server/server.py` | Thread Lifecycle | **MEDIUM** | The `HTTPServer` for Prometheus (Line 259) runs in a daemon thread and is not gracefully joined/stopped, potentially leaving port 9090 bound during restarts. |

