## 2. 🔐 Security Vulnerabilities

| Category | Risk | Severity | Recommendation |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Authentication** | Broken Access Control | **CRITICAL** | The dashboard, API, and `/metrics` are exposed to the public internet/intranet with NO authentication. Any user can view system state or scrape business-sensitive logs. |
| **Integrity** | Webhook Spoofing | **CRITICAL** | `github_webhook` (Line 593) doesn't verify `X-Hub-Signature-256`. An attacker can POST arbitrary failure events to skew drift metrics or trigger malicious retraining. |
| **Execution** | Joblib Deserialization | **HIGH** | `joblib.load` uses `pickle` internally. If the `models/` directory is compromised (e.g., via a supply-chain attack or filesystem access), loading artifacts achieves **Remote Code Execution (RCE)**. |
| **Denial of Service** | Resource Exhaustion | **MEDIUM** | FastAPI endpoints lack `PayloadSizeLimit`. Large log bursts or oversized payloads can exhaust memory on the uvicorn workers. |

